./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0087_1777773260.log:13820: - Added depth-2 listener-review workflow coverage (frac-0086): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/listener_review.py` now exposes typed `ListenerReviewEntry` and `ListenerReviewReport` records plus `parse_review_log(...)`, `build_listener_review_report(...)`, and `summarize_listener_review_report(...)` so operator dashboards and tests can turn the existing listener-review guide/log artifacts into JSON-safe review summaries with parsed entries, action counts, missing-field diagnostics, invalid-action diagnostics, and ablation-CLI reference status. `tests/test_listener_review.py` now includes `ListenerReviewEndToEndTests`, and `tests/test_test_listener_review_depth.py` pins the depth gate and end-to-end class. Existing artifact validation behavior remains compatible; startup identity anchors remain the regression coverage for `bootstrap_identity()` startup hardening, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0087_1777773260.log:13822: - Added depth-2 instrument-patches end-to-end test coverage (frac-0085): `tests/test_instrument_patches.py` now includes `TestInstrumentPatchesEndToEnd`, which drives `select_instrument_patch(...)` cadence/family selection, explicit `patch_name` override, per-role voice normalization across remap, allowed-passthrough, and fallback paths, and JSON-safe palette diagnostics. `tests/test_test_instrument_patches_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/instrument_patches.py` behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path patch-runtime output; startup identity anchors and the targeted test suite remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0087_1777773260.log:13833:+- **Details:** Exploration found the affected surface is `tests/test_lung_capacity_rule.py`, with production behavior in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/lung_capacity.py` and the existing depth-2 report helper coverage in `tests/test_lung_capacity_depth.py`. The production module already implements the simple one-path `apply_lung_capacity(...)` / `analyze_lung_capacity(...)` / `summarize_lung_capacity_report(...)` flow, including inserted breath counts, tagged breath counts, non-applying lanes, scene/song/pattern dispatch, and JSON-safe summaries. This task therefore targets test hardening only: add a depth gate plus a named end-to-end test class that drives the existing public lung-capacity rule surface through inserted, tagged, skipped, summary, direct-rule, and song-aggregation paths. The generated startup hardening bullets target the existing identity startup subsystem; current CLI, first-boot, daemon-ordering, and narrative ASGI tests already cover `bootstrap_identity()` before `FirstBootAnnouncer` and standalone/federated identity persistence, so they will be re-run as regression anchors rather than broadening this lung-capacity test task. No new dependencies, migrations, provider secrets, database columns, runtime state files, HTTP routes, or auth behavior are required.
