":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"I will now\",\"delta\":true}\n+[AGENT] Elapsed: 5m 7s / 10m 0s\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-02T04:41:22.620Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\" draft the verification report, noting the failures in endpoint compatibility, auth header consistency, documentation, and changelog entries.\\n\\n\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-02T04:41:22.804Z\",\"tool_name\":\"write_file\",\"tool_id\":\"write_file_1777696882804_0\",\"parameters\":{\"content\":\"# Verification Report — T-016@20260502t001347za-verify.md\\n\\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\\n**Date:** Friday, May 1, 2026\\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\\n- `scripts/smoke_narrative.py`\\n- `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py`\\n- `src/cypherclaw/narrative_api/app.py`\\n- `README.md`\\n- `CHANGELOG.md`\\n\\n## Correctness\\nThe script `scripts/smoke_narrative.py` correctly implements the requirements stated in the T-016 task description (performs `GET /healthz` and `GET /readyz`, handles `--token` bearer header, uses stdlib only). However, it is **incompatible** with the actual `narrative_api` implementation:\\n- **Endpoints:** The script probes `/healthz` and `/readyz`, but the `narrative_api` (in `src/cypherclaw/narrative_api/app.py`) only exposes `/health`.\\n- **Auth:** The script sends `Authorization: Bearer <token>`, but the `narrative_api` expects `X-Narrative-Auth: <token>` (per T-005).\\n\\n## Completeness\\nThe task is incomplete regarding its integration and documentation:\\n- **Documentation:** The script is not documented in `README.md` as required by the task description (\\\"documented in README so the Deniable operator can validate from the Mac\\\").\\n- **Changelog:** No entry was added to `CHANGELOG.md` for this task.\\n- **Hardening:** The candidate hardening instructions (regression tests for `/world/entities`) are already present in the codebase from previous tasks, but the script itself does not exercise any real narrative endpoints beyond the (incorrect) health checks.\\n\\n## Consistency\\nThe script follows the `image_api` convention (`/healthz`) rather than the `narrative_api` convention (`/health`). The auth header is also inconsistent with the established pattern for this service.\\n\\n## Security\\nThe script correctly avoids logging tokens and uses `urllib.request` safely with a timeout.\\n\\n## Quality\\nThe script is well-structured and uses only the standard library as requested. The accompanying tests in `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` are robust but pass only because they use a mock server that matches the script's incorrect assumptions.\\n\\n## Issues Found\\n- [x] **Incompatible Endpoints — severity: blocking**: Script hits `/healthz` and `/readyz` which do not exist in the target API (`/health`).\\n- [x] **Incompatible Auth Header — severity: blocking**: Script sends `Bearer` token but API expects `X-Narrative-Auth`.\\n- [x] **Missing Documentation — severity: blocking**: Not added to `README.md`.\\n- [x] **Missing Changelog — severity: minor**: No entry in `CHANGELOG.md`.\\n\\n## Verdict: FAIL\\n\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\n1. Update `scripts/smoke_narrative.py` to probe `/health` instead of (or in addition to) `/healthz` and `/readyz`.\\n2. Update the auth header in `scripts/smoke_narrative.py` to use `X-Narrative-Auth` to match the implementation in `narrative_api/app.py`.\\n3. Add usage instructions to `README.md`.\\n4. Add a `CHANGELOG.md` entry for T-016.\\n5. Ensure the script's tests are updated to reflect the actual API endpoints.\\n\",\"file_path\":\"sdp/verification/t-016@20260502t001347za-verify.md\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-02T04:41:22.973Z\",\"tool_id\":\"write_file_1777696882804_0\",\"status\":\"success\"}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-02T04:41:24.665Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"I will commit the verification report for task T-0\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"20