igned with the explicit task contract. The script currently probes only `GET /health` and sets `X-Narrative-Auth` when `--token` is provided. The task requires `GET /healthz` and `GET /readyz`, and optional token handling as a bearer header. Endpoint coverage, token transport format, and URL handling for both checks do not match.\n+`smoke_narrative.py` now matches the task contract:\n+- uses stdlib-only `urllib` + `argparse`\n+- resolves base URL from `NARRATIVE_BASE_URL` with default `http://cypherclaw:8765`\n+- performs `GET /healthz` and `GET /readyz`\n+- sends optional `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n+- prints status + short preview body per endpoint\n+- exits non-zero on any non-2xx or request failure\n \n ## Completeness\n-`/healthz`/`/readyz` checks are not implemented, so the smoke path is incomplete versus the acceptance text. Existing narrative endpoint hardening checks around `GET /world/entities` are present in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` and are not directly impacted by this task.\n+Implementation and focused tests cover required behavior, including both endpoint paths, bearer token propagation, omission of token, and short body previews. Full suite execution succeeded (`3918 passed, 3 skipped`) with the required `pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x` command.\n+\n+The required hardening checks around `GET /world/entities` are present in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` (domain defaults, `domain=deniable`, `type`, and `limit`/`offset` pagination) and are currently passing in suite run.\n \n ## Consistency\n-`/health`/`X-Narrative-Auth` behavior is internally consistent with the deployed narrative API in this repo, but inconsistent with the written task requirement (`/healthz`, `/readyz`, bearer auth). This is a contract mismatch that must be resolved one direction before acceptance.\n+Script behavior is internally consistent and follows the same minimal CLI style as other operator scripts. However, adjacent documentation (`README.md`/`CHANGELOG.md`) still describes the old `/health` + `X-Narrative-Auth` behavior and does not reflect the merged contract.\n \n ## Security\n-No credentials are logged and no non-stdlib runtime dependency is introduced. Error handling is minimal but acceptable for a smoke probe. The current token header choice diverges from the task expectation, which is a functional/contract risk rather than a direct vulnerability.\n+No credentials are logged, no non-stdlib dependencies added, and no filesystem/network secrets are written. Error handling for connection failures is appropriate for a smoke probe.\n \n ## Quality\n-Implementation is clean and test-covered, but tests currently encode the current implementation behavior (`/health` + `X-Narrative-Auth`) and therefore do not validate the requested `/healthz` and `/readyz` behavior. This leaves the delivered functionality below the agreed acceptance criteria.\n+Tests for the CLI are direct and stable. Regression coverage for narrative entity hardening is already in place and passing. Minor documentation drift should be corrected to avoid operator/operator onboarding mismatch.\n \n ## Issues Found\n-- [x] **Wrong endpoints (`/health` only, missing `/healthz` + `/readyz`) — severity: blocking**\n-- [x] **Wrong auth header format (`X-Narrative-Auth` instead of bearer token header) — severity: blocking**\n-- [x] **Acceptance-check gap (`tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` does not exercise requested endpoints) — severity: blocking**\n+- [ ] **Documentation drift — severity: minor:** `README.md` and `CHANGELOG.md` still describe `/health` and `X-Narrative-Auth`, not `/healthz`+`/readyz` and Bearer authorization used by the script.\n \n-## Verdict: FAIL\n+## Verdict: PASS WITH NOTES\n \n ## Notes for Lead Agent\n-1. Update `scripts/smoke_narrative.py` to perform both `GET /healthz` and `GET /readyz`.\n-2. Use optional `--token` as a bearer token header per task requirement.\n-3. Keep default base URL behavior (`NAR