gned ID populated through the shared entity normalization pipeline so the new entity is immediately re-fetchable via `GET /world/entities/{entity_id}`, falls back to the request input for `type`/`name`/`domain`/`properties` when the store returns a partial record, and surfaces HTTP `502` when the store returns no ID, `503` when no store can be constructed, and `422` for whitelist/empty-string violations. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the squad-member round trip via GET, each whitelisted domain, blank/missing-input rejection, downstream-failure handling, missing-store fallback, partial-record fallback, no-ID surfacing, the record-dict signature path, and shared-secret auth behavior.\n\ncommit c9ab03ba958c91d2cbcec4b10258a4484e2cd32c\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Fri May 1 20:41:32 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(narrative-api): apply entity state mutations [T-015@20260502T001347Z]\n\ndiff --git a/CHANGELOG.md b/CHANGELOG.md\nindex 0abdd77..b81a683 100644\n--- a/CHANGELOG.md\n+++ b/CHANGELOG.md\n@@ -2,6 +2,8 @@\n \n ## Unreleased\n \n+- Added the CypherClaw narrative entity mutation endpoint (T-015@20260502T001347Z): `PATCH /world/entities/{entity_id}` now accepts either a wrapped `{\"mutations\": [...]}` body or a single integration-spec `StateMutation` object, applies `set`, `increment`, `decrement`, `append`, and `remove` against entity `properties` paths, validates optional `target_entity` against the path ID, and persists the updated entity through duck-typed deploy-side store methods (`update_entity`/`patch_entity`/`save_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`record_entity`). The route returns the updated `EntityRecord`, surfaces missing entities as `404`, missing stores as `503`, validation failures as `422`, and downstream persistence failures as `502`. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the fighter `current_state` healthy-to-wounded round trip, numeric/list/nested mutation semanti