serialization, validation-before-engine behavior, downstream failure handling, missing-engine fallback, and shared-secret auth behavior.\n\ncommit 2811e086b4e93369ab61f178d76232d842e1b7a3\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Fri May 1 20:10:08 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(narrative_api): implement POST /world/entities [T-014@20260502T001347Z]\n    \n    Adds entity creation endpoint at POST /world/entities accepting\n    {type, name, domain, properties} per PRD CN-008. Domain validated against\n    {shared, cypherclaw, deniable} whitelist before the store is touched. The\n    new create_world_entity() helper duck-types the deploy-side world store\n    across create_entity/add_entity/record_entity/upsert_entity/save_entity\n    (both kwarg-shaped and single-mapping signatures), normalizes the response\n    through the shared entity pipeline, and falls back to request input for\n    absent fields. Returns 201 on success, 422 on validation, 502 on\n    downstream failure or missing store-assigned id, and 503 when no store\n    can be constructed. Round-trip verified via GET /world/entities/{id}.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\ndiff --git a/CHANGELOG.md b/CHANGELOG.md\nindex 041bd71..0abdd77 100644\n--- a/CHANGELOG.md\n+++ b/CHANGELOG.md\n@@ -2,6 +2,8 @@\n \n ## Unreleased\n \n+- Added the CypherClaw narrative entity creation endpoint (T-014@20260502T001347Z): `POST /world/entities` now accepts `{type, name, domain, properties}`, validates `domain` against the `{shared, cypherclaw, deniable}` whitelist before touching the store, and routes through a new `create_world_entity(...)` helper that duck-types the deploy-side world store across `create_entity`/`add_entity`/`record_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`save_entity` (kwarg-shaped or single-mapping signatures). The route returns HTTP `201` with the store-assigned ID populated through the shared entity normalization pipeline so the new entity is immediately re-fetchable